Mlaba, who is SA&#8217;s high commissioner to the UK, is accused of abusing his powers to secure business deals. JOHANNESBURG The department of international relations and cooperation (Dirco) says it's investigating the corruption allegations against South Africa s high commissioner to the United Kingdom, Obed Mlaba.On Sunday morning, the Sunday Times reported that Mlaba has been allegedly abusing his powers to secure business deals.The paper also reported that the high commissioner has been using government letterheads when approaching investors for personal deals.Dirco's Clayson Monyela says it is aware of the allegations. We have noted the story in the media making serious allegations about high commissioner Mlaba, and the department will start a process to check whether there s any truth to those allegations. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)